org.mapstruct.ap.internal.model.source

Class PropertyEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.mapstruct.ap.internal.model.source.PropertyEntry

  • public class PropertyEntry
extends Object
    A PropertyEntry contains information on the name, readAccessor (for source), readAccessor and writeAccessor (for targets) and return type of a property. It can be shared between several nested properties. For example bean nestedMapping1 = "x.y1.z1" nestedMapping2 = "x.y1.z2" nestedMapping3 = "x.y2.z3" has property entries x, y1, y2, z1, z2, z3.
